item.description:
This folder contains a step-by-step IDS login workflow for CMP Acuity UAT. The requests guide you through the authentication process, including:

1. Account login to IDS (STEP 1)
2. IdentityServer authorization callback (STEP 2)
3. Authentication callback to CMP Acuity (STEP 3)

Use this folder to test and validate the full IDS authentication flow for CMP Acuity in the UAT environment.

item.description:
This folder contains requests for creating traditional CMP orders in the Acuity UAT environment.

It focuses specifically on the order creation endpoint, allowing users to test and validate the process of submitting new orders via POST requests to the /Orders/Create API.

item.name: CMP Digital Orders Creation
item.description:
This folder contains requests for creating digital CMP orders in the Acuity UAT environment.

The requests focus on the order creation endpoint (POST [https://cmp-staff.uat.classvaluation.com/Orders/Create](https://cmp-staff.uat.classvaluation.com/Orders/Create)), enabling automated testing and validation of digital order workflows for CMP clients and branches.

item.description:
This folder organizes and groups various CMP order creation workflows specifically for UAT stakeholders.

It includes subfolders for digital, traditional, and integration-based order creation scenarios within the Acuity UAT environment.

Each subfolder represents a distinct workflow, such as iBPO (Land, External, Internal) and iQuant (Internal, External, Desktop) order creation, enabling comprehensive testing and validation of different order creation processes relevant to UAT stakeholders.

item.description:
This folder contains requests for managing the hold status of CMP orders in the Acuity UAT environment.

Use the 'UserActions/Hold' request to place an order on hold, and the 'UserActions/Release_Remove_onHold' request to release an order from hold status.

These endpoints are intended for testing order hold workflows in the Acuity UAT environment.
